## 10. Verdict label note

The auto-emitted verdict label `barcode_hypothesis_supported_with_remaining_aliasing` is **misleading** вЂ” there is no remaining aliasing (all 15 pairs distinguishable). The label triggered because P_ОІ3, P_ОІ4, P_ОІ6 failed; the verdict-label generator conflates "not all predictions held" with "aliasing remains."

A cleaner verdict family for future phases:

- `supported_at_phase_X` вЂ” all predictions hold, no failure modes
- `supported_with_secondary_caveats` вЂ” discrimination established; secondary predictions on compactness / route-sensitivity / slot-coverage need refinement
- `supported_with_remaining_aliasing` вЂ” discrimination partial; some pairs alias
- `not_supported` вЂ” failure mode F1 or F2 fires

The honest Phase ОІ verdict is **`supported_with_secondary_caveats`**.

